added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Cousin of the Creek
added.description: Craig takes his cousin, Bryson, to the Creek, and accidentally starts a water balloon war.

added.title: Fort Williams
added.description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

added.title: Soother or Later
added.description: A terrified Duncan, who's afraid of lightning, learns it's even harder to break back into school than it was to break out when he finally escapes and finds himself in a dark alley with Izzy during a thunderstorm.

added.title: Camping Is in Tents
added.description: A class camping trip turns into a treasure hunt while Harold is determined to catch Bigfoot and keep everyone safe.

added.title: Mutt Ado About Owen
added.description: After accidentally hypnotizing Owen into being a dog, Harold thinks he must reverse the hypnosis to avoid going to jail.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Future Vision
added.description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

added.title: What About Blob?
added.description: Tom turns into a Blob monster and proceeds to eat everything in sight, including the village mice!  Jerry Van Mouseling to the rescue!

added.title: Mouse Party
added.description: Rick and Ginger leave town with instructions for Tom to keep the house in order, but Jerry's got other ideas.

added.title: Maust
added.description: Tom is tricked into helping an evil magician capture all of the mice in the village, but Jerry Van Mouseling foils the magician's plans.

added.title: Tom Prix
added.description: Tom, forced into driving a race car created by evil Dr. Otto, terrorizes the village mice until Jerry Van Mouseling comes to their rescue.

added.title: Hip Replacement
added.description: The neighbor's cat turns out to be a hipster who's laid back attitudes and behaviors are soon adopted by Tom and the other alley cats. Annoyed, Jerry decides to put an end to all of their silly nonsense.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: ThunderSlobs
added.description: Tygra's feeling unappreciated by the other ThunderCats so he starts hanging out with Mumm-Ra and cleaning his Black Pyramid?! Whaaaaaaat?

added.title: Working Grrrl
added.description: Cheetara is the fastest living person in the universe until Monkian beats her in a race?! Now Cheetara has to find something else to be the best at and the rest of the ThunderCats have to find out how Monkian got so darn fast!

added.title: Mandora - The Evil Chaser
added.description: Lion-O "accidentally" releases a whole space prison-full of space criminals and winds up on the wrong side of the law. On the right side of the law is Mandora the Evil Chaser, a no nonsense space cop! Lion-O's gonna have to work real hard to prove he's not a criminal, just a little bit of an oaf!

added.title: Dr. Dometome
added.description: Lion-O is tasked with mapping the beaches of Third Earth, which leads to him somehow draining the oceans of all water entirely. Woops! But a mysterious scientist with a robotic frog says they can fix everything by traveling under the earth, which is just the kinda crazy adventure Lion-O is all about!

added.title: Study Time
added.description: Lion-O never pays attention during Tygra's training sessions so when he's asked to do a pop quiz on "sword magic" he accidentally opens a portal to the Astral Plane and releases the Nether Witch! The Witch imprisons Lion-O and Tygra in her nightmare realm and it's gonna take a lot of studying to figure out a way home. Wonder if the Astral Plane has any great teachers lying around.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Island Adventure
added.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

added.title: My Fair Carol
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad team up to help Carol out with a special occasion.

added.title: The Perfect Meal
added.description: KO teams up with Beardo to make the perfect meal for Carol.

added.title: Sarge in Charge
added.description: Axel and the team must rescue Sarge Charge from a solo mission in the backyard, which Orangutank has turned into his own personal heart of darkness.

added.title: The Other Side
added.description: Axel must 'save' Bobbie Blobby after she defects to Madcap's team, tempted by Porcupunk and his assertion that she belongs with the bad toys.

added.title: Blaze of Glory
added.description: Mega Man and Suna must overcome a sibling dispute over what to do on their day off in order to stop Fire Man from overheating the city.

added.title: Nice on Ice
added.description: An "unscheduled" TV appearance not only lands Aki in hot water for missing class, but sets Ice Man on a misguided mission to "unite" (i.e. freeze together) every human and robot couple in the city!

added.title: Hard Times in Silicon City
added.description: Mega Man must stop Blasto Woman from plundering the Museum of the Hard Age and its cache of military grade weaponry.

added.title: Tripping the Light Fantastic
added.description: Mega Man tries to save Dr. Light from a date with "Mari," who's actually Hypno Woman in disguise!

added.title: Running Wild
added.description: Student elections get blown out of proportion (literally) when Air Man lends his support to Aki's rival for class president, Peter Punk.

added.title: Firstbourne
added.description: Emperor Garmadon has taken control of Ninjago City where Lloyd retreats to the shadows. Meanwhile, the other Ninja and Young Wu are shipwrecked in the Realm of Oni & Dragon and find they are not alone.

added.title: Iron & Stone
added.description: Cole and Young Wu attempt to free their friends, who have been taken captive by a tribe of Dragon Hunters. Meanwhile in Ninjago, Lloyd is reunited with some old friends who may prove valuable allies against Emperor Garmadon.

added.title: Radio Free NinjaGo
added.description: Lloyd must find his voice as he leads a small resistance to capture the airwaves in Ninjago City. Meanwhile in the First Realm, Iron Baron takes the Ninja on a dragon hunt.

added.title: How to Build a Dragon
added.description: While Lloyd and the rebels celebrate their successful strike against Emperor Garmadon, in the Realm of Oni and Dragon, the Ninja dare an elaborate escape from the clutches of Iron Baron and his Dragon Hunters.

added.title: The Gilded Path
added.description: The headquarters to the resistance is breached and Lloyd scrambles to avoid capture. Meanwhile, the Ninja are caught by Heavy Metal, but find an unlikely ally.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee enlists washed-up TV show host Meteorfire to help him find another of Windblade's psychic shards on Luna-3.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 2
added.description: Bumblebee runs the gauntlet of creepily haunted Luna-3, while Meteorfire records everything on camera for his show.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Rigby Goes to Prom
added.description: Rigby asks Eileen to prom. But in order to get there, he has to sneak his Dad's car out of the garage and get it back in one piece.

added.title: Dumped at the Altar
added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Primogenita
added.description: El Emperador Garmadon ha tomado el control de Ciudad Ninjago donde Lloyd se retira hacia las sombras. Mientras tanto, los otros Ninjas y Wu Joven quedan varados en el Reino de Oni y Dragón y descubren que no están solos.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Hierro y piedra
added.description: Cole y Wu Joven intentan liberar a sus amigos, que han sido capturados por una tribu de Cazadores de Dragones. Mientras tanto en Ninjago, Lloyd se reúne con unos viejos amigos que quizás sean aliados valiosos contra el Emperador Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Radio Ninjago libre
added.description: Lloyd deberá encontrar su voz mientras lidera una pequeña resistencia para capturar las señales de transmisión en Ciudad Ninjago. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, el Barón de Hierro lleva a los Ninjas en una cacería de dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Como construir un dragon
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y los rebeldes celebran su exitoso golpe contra el Emperador Garmadon, en el Reino de Oni y Dragón, los Ninjas se aventuran con un elaborado escape de las garras del Barón de Hierro y sus Cazadores de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El camino dorado
added.description: El cuartel general de la resistencia es irrumpido y Lloyd lucha por no ser capturado. Mientras tanto, los Ninjas son capturados por Heavy-Metal, pero encuentran un aliado improbable.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Mi Bella Carol
added.description: K.O., Enid y Rad se unen para ayudar a Carol para una ocasión especial.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Fuerte Williams
added.description: iCuando Craig no puede ir al Arroyo, él y su madre deciden construir el fuerte de cobijas más grande del mundo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Primo del Arroyo
added.description: Craig lleva a su primo Bryson al Arroyo, donde accidentalmente inicia una guerra de globos de agua.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Buscando a Jessica
added.description: Jessica se adentra en un Arroyo desconocido, iy Craig debe encontrarla antes de que su madre se dé cuenta!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Comida Perfecta
added.description: K.O. se alía a Beardo para prepararle la comida perfecta a Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Sarge esta a Cargo
added.description: Axel y el equipo deben rescatar a Sarge Charge de una misión en solitario en el patio trasero, que Orangutank ha convertido en su propio corazón personal de oscuridad.

added.title: Acampar es en tiendas: Primera parte
added.description: Un viaje de campamento se convierte en una búsqueda del tesoro cuando Harold está decidido a atrapar a Pie Grande y mantener a salvo a todos.

added.title: Los ruidos perrunos de Owen
added.description: Después de hipnotizar accidentalmente a Owen y hacerle creer que es un perro, Harold cree que debe revertir la hipnosis para evitar ir a la cárcel.

added.title: La traicion
added.description: Tigro se siente poco apreciado por los demás Thundercats...i¿y por eso empieza a pasar tiempo con Mumm-Ra y a limpiar su Pirámide Negra?!

added.title: A trabajar
added.description: Chitara es el ser vivo más rápido del universo, ihasta que Mandrilok le gana en una carrera! Ahora Chitara tiene que encontrar otra cosa en la cual ser la mejor, imientras el resto de los Thundercats descubren cómo Mandrilok se volvió tan increíblemente rápido!

added.title: El Otro Lado
added.description: Axel debe "salvar" a Bobbie Blobby después de que ella se dañe al equipo de Madcap, tentado por Porcupunk y su afirmación de que ella pertenece a los juguetes malos.

added.title: Un Dragon en la Guarderia
added.description: Duncan finalmente logra escapar solo para descubrir que ha olvidado su chupete y necesita entrar a la escuela para recuperarlo.

added.title: Acampar es en tiendas: Segunda parte
added.description: Un viaje de campamento se convierte en una búsqueda del tesoro cuando Harold está decidido a atrapar a Pie Grande y mantener a salvo a todos.
